# Privacy Policy

## 1. Data Collection
* **User Data:** V.E.C.T.O.R. // CITADEL does not collect, store, or profile data from general server members.
* **Message Content:** The Service processes message content strictly in real-time to execute administrative workflows and authorized commands. Message text is never written to persistent logs, databases, or external storage.
* **Metadata:** Minimal volatile Discord identifiers (such as User IDs) are checked against a local hardcoded allowlist solely to enforce access control.

## 2. Data Storage and Retention
No personal data, chat history, or server metrics are retained, tracking-pushed, or stored persistently. All operational data exists strictly within volatile memory (RAM) during runtime execution and is purged immediately upon task completion.

## 3. Third-Party Sharing
No data is ever shared, sold, or transmitted to third-party entities, external databases, or cloud analytics platforms.

## 4. Contact & Inquiries
For infrastructure or system-wide security queries regarding this private instance, contact the server administrator directly.
